    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-06-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="400"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Romero</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. F. W.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexican Legation in the United States of
                                America,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-06-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 25, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Assistant Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to
                    acknowledge the receipt of the note which you were pleased to address to me, of
                    yesterday’s date, enclosing a copy of a communication from Hon. Hugh McCulloch,
                    Secretary of the Treasury, of the 22d, in relation to the steamer which has been
                    placed at the disposal of the wife of President Juarez, for the purpose of
                    conveying her from New Orleans to Vera Cruz.</p>
                <p>I have this day communicated your note, referred to, to Mrs. Juarez, and the
                    document annexed thereto, and she requests me to express her thanks to you for
                    the attention which you have shown in transmitting to her the letter of the
                    Secretary of the Treasury, and to inform you that in the course of the week she
                    expects to set off for New Orleans.</p>
                <p>I avail myself of this opportunity to renew to you, sir, the assurances of my
                    distinguished consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M. ROMERO.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">F. W. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
